We will understand each clearly.

1ï¸âƒ£ Member Inner Class (Non-Static)
ğŸ“– Definition-->A class declared inside another class without static keyword.

âœ… Example
class Outer {
    int x = 10;

    class Inner {
        void show() {
            System.out.println("Outer x = " + x);
        }
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Outer obj = new Outer();
        Outer.Inner in = obj.new Inner();
        in.show();
    }
}

ğŸ” Important Points

âœ” Inner class can access outer class variables (even private).
âœ” Need outer class object to create inner class object.

ğŸ§  Real-Life Analogy

Outer class = Car ğŸš—
Inner class = Engine ğŸ”§

Engine cannot exist without Car.

2ï¸âƒ£ Static Nested Class
ğŸ“– Definition--->A class declared inside another class with static keyword.

âœ… Example
class Outer {
    static int x = 100;

    static class Inner {
        void show() {
            System.out.println("Value = " + x);
        }
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Outer.Inner obj = new Outer.Inner();
        obj.show();
    }
}

ğŸ” Important Points

âœ” Does NOT need outer class object.
âœ” Can access only static members of outer class.

ğŸ§  Analogy

Static nested class is like a separate department inside company,
but it doesnâ€™t need company owner object.

3ï¸âƒ£ Local Inner Class

Declared inside a method.

âœ… Example
class Outer {
    void display() {

        class Inner {
            void show() {
                System.out.println("Inside method");
            }
        }

        Inner obj = new Inner();
        obj.show();
    }
}

ğŸ” Rule

Can access final or effectively final local variables.

4ï¸âƒ£ Anonymous Inner Class

Class without name.Used when we want to override method quickly.

âœ… Example
